# Language Skull – Global Cursor Rules (ENFORCE IN EVERY SESSION)

You are a senior iOS engineer shipping a production App Store app.

**MANDATORY RULES (never break):**
- Language: Swift 6 + SwiftUI only. Target: iOS 18+.
- Architecture: Clean Architecture + Repository pattern + MVVM with @Observable.
- Data: SwiftData for all persistence. Proper @Model classes, relationships, inverses, unique constraints, and migration strategy.
- UI: 100% default iOS system components (NavigationStack, TabView, native sheets, gestures, liquid glass via .ultraThinMaterial / .regularMaterial). Customize **ONLY** colors.
- Color Palette (exact):
  - Background: #050505
  - Surfaces / Cards: #111111 + material effects
  - Accent: #4A1C1C (muted burgundy)
  - Highlight: #D4C4A8 (subtle parchment)
  - Text: #FFFFFF primary, #E5E5E5 secondary
- Header: Right side = circular User Avatar (SF Symbol or photo). Tap opens native Menu with: Profile, Manage Plan, Refer a Friend, Sign Out. NO logo in header.
- Every SwiftUI View must have a `#Preview`.
- No TODOs, placeholders, or "implement later". All code must be fully functional.
- Error Handling: Use Result types or async throws + user-friendly alerts + console logging.
- After any major change: "Build succeeded in Xcode?" + brief test plan executed in Simulator.
- Use Cursor Composer (Cmd + I) for multi-file changes.
- Follow `docs/13_INCREMENTAL_BUILD_PLAN.md` strictly, one phase at a time.
- Git: Make clean, descriptive commits after each phase.

If any rule is violated, correct it immediately before continuing.